@prefix : <https://www.somusicvocabulary.org/music#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

# NEGATIVE: :WrittenByShape — THE BYPASS.
#
# The credit guards were originally hung off :SongShape / :AlbumShape / :CompositionShape,
# i.e. anchored to the WORK'S CLASS. Nothing in the TBox stops an :Album carrying :writtenBy,
# and :AlbumShape never mentioned :writtenBy — so this exact graph passed with ZERO
# violations. An album "written by" a record label. The central new guarantee of v3.0.0
# ("a credit requires the matching role") was bypassable by picking a different work type.
#
# The guards are now anchored with sh:targetSubjectsOf on the PROPERTY, so the rule follows
# the credit wherever it is used. This fixture is the regression test for that.

:NEG_LabelWriter a :RecordLabel ;
    rdfs:label "Negative fixture — a record label"@en ;
    .

:NEG_AlbumWithLyricist a :Album ;
    rdfs:label "Negative fixture — an ALBUM written by a record label"@en ;
    :writtenBy :NEG_LabelWriter ;
    .
